<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="8" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,1459,1744]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1892" box="[232,347,1459,1482]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Episimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[232,347,1459,1482]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Episimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes 67 described species in the New World, ranging from the 
<collectingCountry box="[1157,1209,1459,1483]" name="United States of America" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">U.S.</collectingCountry>
south to 
<collectingCountry box="[1322,1387,1459,1483]" name="Chile" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Chile</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[192,319,1491,1515]" name="Argentina" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, plus two species from the Afrotropical Region (
<bibRefCitation author="Gilligan, T. M. &amp; J. Baixeras &amp; J. W. Brown" box="[906,1147,1491,1515]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref8315" refString="Gilligan, T. M., J. Baixeras, and J. W. Brown. 2018. T @ RTS: Online World Catalogue of the Tortricidae (Ver. 4.0). Available at http: // www. tortricid. net / catalogue. asp. (Last accessed 15 December 2018.)" type="url" year="2018">Gilligan et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Hosts are recorded for about a dozen species (
<bibRefCitation author="Brown, J. W. &amp; G. Robinson &amp; J. A. Powell" box="[472,694,1524,1548]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" refId="ref7873" refString="Brown, J. W., G. Robinson, and J. A. Powell. 2008. Food plant database of the leafrollers of the world (Lepidoptera: Tortricidae) (Version 1.0). Available at http: // www. tortricid. net / foodplants. asp. (Last accessed 1 January 2019.)" type="url" year="2008">Brown et al. 2008</bibRefCitation>
), and those with more than a single host record appear to be polyphagous. For example, the widespread North American species 
<taxonomicName authority="(Clemens, 1860)" baseAuthorityName="Clemens" baseAuthorityYear="1860" box="[1024,1389,1557,1581]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Episimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argutanus">
<emphasis box="[1024,1184,1557,1580]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">E. argutanus</emphasis>
(Clemens, 1860)
</taxonomicName>
has been reared from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="R.Brown" authorityYear="1818" box="[418,601,1589,1613]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Anacardiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Sapindales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Anacardiaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="A.M.C.Dumeril" authorityYear="1805" box="[615,752,1590,1614]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="S.F.Gray" authorityYear="1822" box="[767,905,1589,1613]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Betulaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fagales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Betulaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[920,1099,1589,1613]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caprifoliaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Dipsacales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Caprifoliaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Durande" authorityYear="1782" box="[1113,1235,1589,1613]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Ericaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[1250,1436,1589,1613]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Euphorbiaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Abel" authorityYear="1817" box="[192,407,1622,1646]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Hamamelidaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Saxifragales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Hamamelidaceae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[418,533,1622,1645]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Rosaceae</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="C.F.Mirbel" authorityYear="1815" box="[599,724,1622,1646]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ulmaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Ulmaceae</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="9.[192,1440,1459,1744]" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">
Three specimens of 
<taxonomicName authority="Razowski and Wojtusiak, 2006" authorityName="Razowski and Wojtusiak" authorityYear="2006" box="[483,1246,1654,1679]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Episimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brunneomarginatus">
<emphasis box="[483,852,1654,1678]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Episimus brunneomarginatus</emphasis>
Razowski and Wojtusiak, 2006
</taxonomicName>
were reared in 
<collectingCountry box="[192,296,1687,1711]" name="Ecuador" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
, one from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1753" box="[416,495,1687,1711]" class="Insecta" family="Clusiidae" genus="Clusia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[416,495,1687,1711]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Clusia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sp. (
<taxonomicName authorityName="J.Lindley" authorityYear="1830" box="[548,682,1687,1711]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Clusiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Clusiaceae</taxonomicName>
), one from an unidentified 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gaudichaud-Beaupre" authorityYear="1835" box="[999,1119,1688,1711]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Moraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Moraceae</taxonomicName>
, and one from an unknown host. A second species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Walsingham" authorityYear="1892" box="[498,613,1720,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Episimus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[498,613,1720,1743]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="8">Episimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(undetermined) also was reared from an unknown host.
</paragraph>
